canonical:
  title: 平章崔濡辭知貢擧不允
  author: 崔諴
  language: lzh
  text: 朕若稽前古紹述大猷閒年而特下詔書數路以旁招多士盖考之以文章氣力之高下或試之以經術義理之淺深至陰陽卜筮之流醫律書筭之技惟主張於公選宜委任於宗工卿望重鈞衡學窮墳典嘗倅司於貢擧能揀取於賢才所以斷自朕心授之文柄是猶師曠聽而雅鄭之聲辨伯樂顧而駑驥之價分玆爲注意之愈深行見得人之實効勉膺重命無復過謙
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 平章崔濡辭知貢擧不允
  author: 崔諴
  language: lzh
  text: 朕若稽前古。紹述大猷。閒年而特下詔書。數路以旁招多士。盖考之以文章氣力之高下。或試之以經術義理之淺深。至陰陽卜筮之流。醫律書筭之技。惟主張於公選。宜委任於宗工。卿望重鈞衡。學窮墳典。嘗倅司於貢擧。能揀取於賢才。所以斷自朕心。授之文柄。是猶師曠聽而雅鄭之聲辨。伯樂顧而駑驥之價分。玆爲注意之愈深。行見得人之實効。勉膺重命。無復過謙。
korean:
  title: 평장 최유 사 지공거 불윤
  author: 최함
  language: kor
  text: 짐이 예전의 일을 상고하고 선대의 큰 계획을 계승하여, 격년으로 특별히 조서를 내려서 몇 도에서 두루 선비들을 불렀다. 대개 문장(文章)과 기력(氣力)의 고하(高下)를 고사하고, 더러는 경술(經術)과 의리(義理)의 천심(淺深)을 시험하며, 음양 복서(陰陽卜筮) 따위와 의율 서산(醫律書算)의 기술까지 뽑기 위한 것으로, 오직 공정하게 선발하여야 하는바, 마땅히 대신에게 위임하여야 한다.경의 명망은 재상의 자리에서 무거우며, 학업은 분전(墳典)을 궁리했다. 일찍이 공거(貢擧)를 맡아서 능히 어진 인재를 선택하였다. 이에 짐이 마음으로부터 결단해서 경에게 문병(文柄)을 주는 바이다. 이는 사광(師曠 춘추 시대의 음악가)이 들어야 아(雅)와 정(鄭)의 소리가 분변이 되고, 백락(伯樂)이 돌아봐야 둔한 말과 천리마의 가치가 갈라지는 것과 같은 것이다. 주의를 더욱 깊게 하여 장차 인재를 얻는 실효를 보자는 것이다. 그러니 힘써 중대한 명을 받아서 다시 과도한 겸양이 없을지어다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0320_020_0090&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Edict Appointing Choe Yu as Director of the Civil Examination
  author: Choe Ham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I have studied the practices of antiquity and seek to continue the great designs of my predecessors. Thus I have issued special edicts at regular intervals, summoning talented scholars from every province. I examine them by the excellence of their literary compositions and the depth of their natural abilities. Some I test through their knowledge of the classics and the subtleties of their reasoning. Even those skilled in yin-yang divination, medicine, law, and mathematics—all such talents must be selected with utmost fairness and entrusted to those most capable of discerning merit.

    Your reputation stands high in the halls of state, and your learning has penetrated the depths of ancient texts. You have long served in the selection of gifted men and have proven yourself able to recognize true talent. Therefore, I now place my trust in you and grant you the authority to choose. As Shi Kuang could distinguish the refined from the vulgar in music once he had heard it, and as Bo Le could judge the swift from the slow once he had seen them—so too shall your discernment bring forth genuine talent. Let this decision reflect my careful deliberation. I expect to see the true fruits of finding the worthy. Accept this great responsibility with resolve, and harbor no further modesty in your acceptance.
  footnotes:
    - Shi Kuang (師曠) was a legendary musician of the Spring and Autumn period known for his perfect ear for music and his ability to detect even subtle flaws in sound.
    - Bo Le (伯樂) was a legendary horse trainer of ancient times, famously able to identify superior horses; the term became synonymous with a talent scout or judge of ability.
    - The 'civil examination' (貢擧) refers to the classical Chinese system of recruiting officials through merit-based testing.
